2026-04-21 01:27:34 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['PSU-to-control cable pair', 'Control-to-load cable pair'] hypothesis_explanation='Both interfaces are wired with reversed polarity: the PSU’s + output is connected to the control module’s − input (and vice versa), and the control module’s + output is connected to the load module’s − input (and vice versa). In this condition, the series diode in the load module remains reverse‑biased, so no current flows through either the main lamp or the internal lamp indicator, and the lamp never turns on when the switch is operated. The power‑supply LED is still lit because it is directly across the PSU terminals, and the control module’s inverted‑cables LED is off because there is no net 12 V difference in the sense direction that forward‑biases that LED/resistor pair. Correcting the polarity at both cable interfaces (reconnecting + to + and − to −) should restore normal operation.'
